		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Posthoc_Prior">Posthoc_Prior</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~Posthoc_Prior">( 7057067 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64733562"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64733562"><p>Sorry for the double post. But, I forgot to include this: Telegram uses the cryptography standard called MTProto. It's been found to be insecure. Specifically, it's been found that you can use a ciphertext from Telegram and use that to turn it into a different ciphertext that decrypts the original message</p><p>Here's the <a href="https://eprint.iacr.org/2015/1177.pdf" title="iacr.org" rel="nofollow">link</a> [iacr.org]to the paper that discovered this vulnerability.</p></div>
	</div>

